The clearest movement came where federal power was turned against disfavored regions and communities. The president\'92s earlier executive orders targeting sanctuary cities were now backed by practice. ICE raids swept through Los Angeles swap meets, Home Depot parking lots, and Latino parishes, detaining not only undocumented workers but also U.S. citizens and blocking lawyers and members of Congress from seeing detainees. In Florida, agents raided grocery stores, churches, and schools in Lake Worth Beach, leaving the Guatemalan\uc0\u8209 Maya Center to report that many of its clients had been deported or ordered to self\u8209 deport. These were not isolated operations. They were part of a campaign the president explicitly framed as an assault on \'93Democrat Power Centers,\'94 with Los Angeles, Chicago, and New York singled out as targets.\
