Elsewhere, elected officials treated protest itself as suspect. Florida\'92s governor told drivers they could legally run over protesters if they felt threatened while surrounded by a crowd, a statement that blurred the line between self\uc0\u8209 defense and vigilantism. A group of journalists, legal observers, and protesters responded by suing the Department of Homeland Security and its secretary, alleging that federal forces had used excessive force to suppress First Amendment rights. The courts had not yet resolved that suit, but its filing showed that civil society still looked to law as a shield, even as law was increasingly used as a club.\
