Information itself became a contested terrain. The Pentagon\'92s rapid response team, under Secretary Hegseth, used official social\uc0\u8209 media accounts to promote his agenda and attack reporters, blurring the line between public communication and partisan messaging. Right\u8209 wing media figures and influencers spread false claims that the Minnesota lawmaker assassin was a left\u8209 wing \'93Marxist\'94 tied to the Democratic governor, despite evidence of his right\u8209 leaning politics and anti\u8209 abortion views. Senator Mike Lee amplified similar misinformation to millions of viewers before deleting his posts, but he did not correct the record. The president again called for a special prosecutor to investigate the 2020 election, insisting it had been stolen in a \'93landslide,\'94 and demanded that the truth be \'93finally\'94 revealed, even as no credible evidence supported his claims. Disinformation became a standing feature, not a campaign tactic.\
